Is  this something inherent to `thread_local` to construct on first use?

Running this example program:

```cpp
struct Foo {
    Mutex m_mut;
    Foo()
    {
        std::cout << __LINE__ << __func__ << std::endl;
        LOCK(m_mut);
    }
    ~Foo()
    {
        std::cout << __LINE__ << __func__ << std::endl;
        LOCK(m_mut);
    }
};

void initialize()
{
}

void test_one_input(const std::vector<uint8_t>& buffer)
{
    static Foo bar;
}
```

gives me

```
14Foo
80LockStack
84~LockStack
19~Foo
```

